        <h2>Organization</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The examination will take place on Tuesday, October 29, 2018 from 14:00 to 19:00 in the MA 10E MA 10F rooms.
                Always check the official calender for last minute changes: <a
                        href="https://se.timeedit.net/web/lu/db1/lth1/ri1X50gQ3560YfQQ15Z5778Y0Zy7007335Y57Q545.html">
                    timeedit</a>.
            </li>
            <li>You must register to the examination as you do for the other examinations. <!--The registration is open
                from
                October 3 to October 17.-->
            </li>
            <li>The examination will consist of two parts:
                <ol>
                    <li>Examination questions, where the candidate will have to explain or define terms relevant to the
                        course. In this part, no document will be allowed except bilingual dictionaries, for instance
                        Chinese-English or Swedish-English. Scientific calculators are also allowed.
                    </li>
                    <li>In the second part, you will have to reimplement a natural language processing
                        system from
                        a scientific article. This will include programming, where the candidate will use
                        Python
                        or a java-like algorithmic language. In this part, the textbook, copies of the slides, copies of
                        the
                        lab programs, a Python handbook, a Java handbook, and a Perl handbook will be allowed.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>
